{"word":"ἄνανδρος","slug":"ἄνανδρος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄνανδρος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀνήρ'><el>ἀνήρ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>= <el>ἄνευ ἀνδρός</el> <i>husbandless</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>= <el>ἄνευ ἀνδρῶν</el>, <i>without men</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>wanting in manhood, unmanly</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>τὸ ἄνανδρον  ἀνανδρία</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}